text: i need to stop reading twitter
i ordered a Circle to use parental controls against myself so i stop reading news at home at all hours
will report back and probably write a blog post about it
Me too, my anxiety is through the roof and twitter used to be my reprieve. Now it's just egging me on and i have no digital escape. I have to resort to hanging out irl with my wife

i was discussing items like that w matty while we were on vacation. how i wanted to get away from it, but how hard it is if you use your digital consumption to inform you.. but then also the consumption as an escape? blerg.
My hope is I can like, block cnn and twitter from... 9PM-730AM. may have to be all internet, we'll see
currently describing my use case to a poor disney CSR

honestly, that level of anxiety and confusion is part of the strategy. My counter has been on 2 daily actions, which helps focus my media consumption to getting educated:
1) Reach out to someone daily. Call the State House, Congress, a family member in another district, send a thank you note, contact an organization who can help (e.g. ACLU, SPLC) to find out what actions I can take.
2) Read the source material for at least 1 issue. The other day, it was the text of the immigration EO (and the annotated version). Once legislation starts hitting the House and Senate committees I want to make sure I'm well-read on the text that's being debated.
that said, I'm like a moth to a flame
ooooh! I have a friend at circle, if needed. <@U06DFL7BP>
